A close ally of Embu Senator Lenny Kivuti with whom he had defected with to Maendeleo Chap Chap has gone back to Jubilee Party.Mbeere North MP Charles Njagagua had, in most cases, agreed with Kivuti&rsquo;s political decisions. He defected from Jubilee together with Kivuti and Deputy Governor Dorothy Nditi in early February.But yesterday, the MP told the Star on the phone that he has returned back home after going astray into Maendeleo Chap Chap.Njagagua said he wants to campaign for President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s reelection, because of his good development record.He said he found out he could not do so in another party, except in Jubilee.Njagagua said most of his constituents are in Jubilee Party and because they are his employers, he has to be where they are.